"748","<TEXT>"
"749","In late 2003 and 2004, Putnam Management settled charges brought"
"750","by the SEC and the Massachusetts Securities"
"751","Division in connection with excessive short-term trading in"
"752","Putnam funds. In July 2011, the fund recorded a receivable"
"753","of $465,203 related to restitution payments in connection with a"
"754","distribution plan approved by the SEC. This"
"755","amount is reported in the Increase in capital from settlement"
"756","payments line on the Statement of changes in net"
"757","assets. These allegations and related matters have served as the"
"758","general basis for certain lawsuits, including"
"759","purported class action lawsuits against Putnam Management and, in"
"760","a limited number of cases, some Putnam"
"761","funds. In May 2011, the fund received a payment of $10,946 related to"
"762","settlement of those lawsuits. This amount is"
"763","reported in the Increase in capital from settlement payments line"
"764","on the Statement of changes in net assets."
"765","Putnam Management has agreed to bear any costs incurred by the"
"766","Putnam funds as a result of these matters."
